00:55.554 --> 00:57.851
"Always watch the blade." I got it.

00:57.854 --> 00:59.556
Wow. I'm impressed.

00:59.558 --> 01:01.224
You fight like your grandfather.

01:01.226 --> 01:02.759
Mom, we're practicing.

01:02.761 --> 01:04.694
Actually, we just finished.

01:04.696 --> 01:07.163
Like I told you... always
keep your eye on the blade.

01:07.165 --> 01:09.399
What's the point? I'm
never gonna be good enough.

01:13.166 --> 01:14.532
What's going on with him lately?

01:16.701 --> 01:18.667
I think you know, Emma.

01:18.670 --> 01:20.009
He's almost grown.

01:20.011 --> 01:21.578
He's about to leave home, isn't he?

01:23.748 --> 01:24.781
Aye.

01:24.783 --> 01:26.035
I'm gonna go talk to him.

01:26.038 --> 01:27.237
What, to stop him?

01:27.240 --> 01:29.052
I missed so much already.
I don't want to...

01:29.054 --> 01:32.722
This isn't an ending, Emma.

01:32.724 --> 01:34.524
There's more to come.

01:34.526 --> 01:35.792
But we don't know for sure.

01:35.794 --> 01:37.894
What if I don't get a second chance?

01:37.896 --> 01:39.629
It's gonna be okay.

01:39.631 --> 01:42.198
I have something to make
things a little less terrifying.

01:47.138 --> 01:49.572
A little bottle of rum?
Because I wouldn't say no.

01:49.574 --> 01:51.407
It's a little bottle of magic.

01:51.409 --> 01:54.333
You speak your message in here,

01:54.341 --> 01:56.679
add the name of your favorite
pirate, drop it in the water,

01:56.681 --> 01:58.982
and before you can say "Yo-ho-ho,"

01:58.984 --> 02:00.450
it'll find the person you seek.

02:00.452 --> 02:01.618
A message in a bottle.

02:01.620 --> 02:03.186
Mm-hmm.

02:03.188 --> 02:04.520
Thank you.

02:04.522 --> 02:06.189
Look, he's grown into a fine young lad,

02:06.191 --> 02:09.268
and he is lucky to
have a mother like you.

02:09.270 --> 02:12.038
He's lucky to have a pirate like you.

02:16.067 --> 02:18.434
He's gonna be fine.

02:36.148 --> 02:38.254
That's the man who helped Cinderella

02:38.256 --> 02:39.956
kill our beloved prince.

02:39.958 --> 02:41.057
She didn't kill him.

02:41.059 --> 02:42.926
The royal family disagrees.

02:42.928 --> 02:44.688
Where is she? Tell me.

02:44.691 --> 02:46.115
Never.

02:46.118 --> 02:48.097
So...

02:48.099 --> 02:50.366
You're in love with her.

02:50.368 --> 02:51.534
Didn't say that.

02:51.536 --> 02:53.336
You were spotted with
something of hers...

02:53.338 --> 02:54.771
A glass slipper.

02:54.773 --> 02:56.773
Give it to me, and you can live.

02:56.775 --> 02:58.241
Sorry, lady, I hid it.

02:58.243 --> 03:00.209
And you're not gonna get it.

03:00.211 --> 03:02.812
Although... I do have
something else made of glass.

03:02.814 --> 03:04.380
And that bottle's going to save you?

03:04.382 --> 03:05.982
Not all by itself.

03:05.984 --> 03:07.784
Help. I've been captured
by Lady Tremaine.

03:07.786 --> 03:10.086
-Stop him. 
-Send Emma, Regina, and Captain Hook.

03:10.088 --> 03:11.177
Stop him!

03:13.625 --> 03:20.891
